(1660, 'Collect and review historical head-to-head matchups data between the Jaguars and Titans to understand past performance trends.', 'Historical Analysis Agent', 'Medium', '2024-12-08 18:34:29', 38, 1, 'To understand the historical head-to-head matchups between the Jacksonville Jaguars and the Tennessee Titans, here are some key factual points gathered from credible sources:\n\n## Overall Head-to-Head Record\n- The Jaguars and Titans have played a total of 59 games, including one postseason game. The Titans lead the overall series 35-24 (59.3%)[2][3].\n- In regular season games only, the Titans have a 34-24 (58.6%) record against the Jaguars[2].\n\n## Recent Performance\n- In the last 10 games (2019-2023), the Titans have a 6-4 record against the Jaguars[2].\n- The Jaguars last swept both games against the Titans in the 2022 season, winning 36-22 on the road in Week 14 and 20-16 at home in Week 18[1].\n- The Titans last swept both games against the Jaguars in the 2021 season, winning 37-19 on the road in Week 5 and 20-0 at home in Week 14[2].\n\n## Recent Matches\n- The last game between the two teams was on January 7, 2024, where the Titans won 28-20 at home against the Jaguars[1][2][3].\n- In their previous meeting on November 19, 2023, the Jaguars won 34-14 at home against the Titans[1][2][3].\n\n## Historical Trends\n- The longest all-time winning streak for the Jaguars over the Titans is 4 games, which occurred from December 8, 1996, to September 27, 1998[1].\n- The Titans have had a 5-game winning streak over the Jaguars three separate times[2].\n\n## Upcoming Game Context\n- The upcoming game on December 8, 2024, will be played at the Titans\' home stadium[1][2].\n\nThese historical trends and recent performance data provide a factual basis for understanding the past dynamics between the Jaguars and Titans, but do not predict the outcome of the upcoming game.', '[\"https:\\/\\/champsorchumps.us\\/team\\/nfl\\/jacksonville-jaguars\\/head-to-head\\/tennesse