(1667, 'Gather historical head-to-head performance data between Seahawks and Cardinals, including win-loss records, score margins, and locations of the games.', 'Data Gathering Agent', 'High', '2024-12-08 18:34:36', 39, 1, 'To inform the analysis of the upcoming NFL game between the Seattle Seahawks and the Arizona Cardinals on Sunday, December 8th, here are some key historical head-to-head performance data points:\n\n## Overall Head-to-Head Record\n- The Seattle Seahawks lead the overall series 28-22-1 against the Arizona Cardinals[1][2][3].\n\n## Recent Performance\n- The Seahawks have a current 6-game winning streak against the Cardinals, which started on January 9, 2022, with a 38-30 win and is still active[1][2][3].\n- In the last 20 games, the Cardinals are 6-13-1 against the Seahawks[4].\n\n## Score Margins and Recent Games\n- The last game between the two teams was on November 24, 2024, where the Seahawks won 16-6 at home against the Cardinals[1][2][3].\n- In the 2023 season, the Seahawks swept both games against the Cardinals, winning 20-10 at home and 21-20 on the road[1][2].\n- Recent scores include:\n  - Week 7, 2023: Seahawks won 20-10 at home[1][2][3].\n  - Week 18, 2023: Seahawks won 21-20 on the road[1][2].\n  - Week 6, 2022: Seahawks won 19-9 at home[1][2][3].\n  - Week 9, 2022: Seahawks won 31-21 on the road[1][2][3].\n\n## Locations of Games\n- The teams have played each other at both Lumen Field (Seahawks\' home) and State Farm Stadium (Cardinals\' home)[3].\n- The upcoming game on December 8, 2024, is scheduled to be played at State Farm Stadium, the home of the Arizona Cardinals[2][3].\n\n## Historical Context\n- The longest all-time winning streak for the Seahawks against the Cardinals is the current 6-game streak. For the Cardinals, their longest winning streak was 5 games, which occurred from 1976 to 1995[1][2][3].\n- The teams have never met in the NFL playoffs[1][2][3].\n\nThis historical data provides a factual basis for understanding the