(1684, 'Gather historical game performance data for the Buffalo Bills and Los Angeles Rams over the current and past three seasons.', 'Data Gathering Agent', 'High', '2024-12-08 18:34:55', 41, 1, 'To inform the analysis of the upcoming NFL game between the Buffalo Bills and the Los Angeles Rams on Sunday, December 8th, here are some historical and recent performance data points from credible sources:\n\n## Head-to-Head Record\n- The Buffalo Bills lead the series against the Los Angeles Rams with a 9-5 record in their 14 matchups[2][3][5].\n- The Bills have a current three-game winning streak against the Rams, with their last victory being a 31-10 win in Week 1 of the 2022 season[2][3][5].\n\n## Recent Performance (2022 Season)\n- In the last game between the two teams on September 8, 2022, the Bills dominated the Rams 31-10. Josh Allen threw for 297 yards, had 3 passing TDs and 1 rushing TD, and achieved a perfect passer rating in the second half. The Bills\' defense sacked Matthew Stafford seven times without blitzing[1][2][3].\n\n## Recent Season Statistics (2024 and Past Seasons)\n- **Buffalo Bills:**\n  - As of the last update, the Bills have been performing strongly, having clinched the AFC East and averaging 38 points per game over their last three games, including playoffs, in the 2022 season[2].\n  - Josh Allen has continued to improve, ranking 14th in total passing yards this season with 2,691 yards[2].\n\n- **Los Angeles Rams:**\n  - Matthew Stafford ranks 7th in total passing yards this season with 2,983 yards[2].\n  - The Rams have been struggling, on a three-game losing streak and needing a win to keep their playoff hopes alive[2].\n\n## Defensive and Offensive Performance\n- In the 2022 game, the Bills\' defense was highly effective, with Von Miller recording a pass rush win rate of 47%, and the team sacking Matthew Stafford seven times without blitzing. DT Jordan Phillips led the team with 6 QB pressures, more than the entire Rams defense combined[1].