(1736, 'Review special teams performance statistics for both the Jaguars and Titans, as this can play a pivotal role in game outcomes.', 'Special Teams Analysis Agent', 'Medium', '2024-12-08 18:42:22', 38, 1, 'To assess the special teams performance of the Jacksonville Jaguars and the Tennessee Titans, here are some key statistics and insights from credible sources:\n\n## Jaguars Special Teams Performance\n- In the 2024 NFL special teams scoring statistics, the Jaguars have:\n  - 17 points scored on special teams.\n  - A field goal percentage of 89.5%.\n  - 19 field goals attempted and 100% of extra points made.\n  - No blocked kicks or returns for touchdowns against them, but they have one return touchdown[1].\n- The Jaguars\' special teams performance is notable for their efficiency in field goals and extra points.\n\n## Titans Special Teams Performance\n- For the Tennessee Titans:\n  - They have 19 points scored on special teams.\n  - A field goal percentage of 95%.\n  - 22 field goals attempted and 100% of extra points made.\n  - No blocked kicks or returns for touchdowns against them[1].\n- The Titans also show strong performance in field goal accuracy and extra point conversions.\n\n## Additional Context\n- In terms of overall special teams rankings, the Detroit Lions are ranked as the best in special teams according to ESPN\'s FPI rankings, but specific rankings for the Jaguars and Titans are not provided in the sources. However, the general statistics indicate both teams have solid special teams units, particularly in kicking accuracy[2].\n\n## Summary\nBoth the Jacksonville Jaguars and the Tennessee Titans exhibit strong special teams performance, especially in field goal and extra point conversions. The Jaguars have a slight edge in scoring from special teams with 17 points compared to the Titans\' 19 points, but both teams have high field goal percentages and perfect extra point conversion rates. These statistics suggest that special teams could play a cr