(1737, 'Evaluate rest periods and potential fatigue by reviewing the number of days off both teams have had leading into the game.', 'Fatigue and Recovery Analysis Agent', 'Low', '2024-12-08 18:42:22', 38, 1, 'To evaluate the rest periods and potential fatigue for the Jacksonville Jaguars and the Tennessee Titans leading into their game on Sunday, December 8, 2024, here are the relevant factual points:\n\n## Bye Weeks\n- The Tennessee Titans had their bye week in Week 5 of the 2024 NFL season, along with the Detroit Lions, Los Angeles Chargers, and Philadelphia Eagles[3].\n- The Jacksonville Jaguars had their bye week in Week 12, along with several other teams including the Atlanta Falcons, Buffalo Bills, Cincinnati Bengals, New Orleans Saints, and New York Jets[3].\n\n## Recent Games and Rest Periods\n- The Jaguars played their last game on December 1, 2024, against the Houston Texans, which means they have had 7 days of rest before the game against the Titans[4].\n- The Titans played their last game on December 1, 2024, against the Washington Commanders, which also gives them 7 days of rest before the game against the Jaguars[4].\n\n## Conclusion\nBoth the Jacksonville Jaguars and the Tennessee Titans have had an equal amount of rest, each having 7 days off since their last games. There is no indication from the bye week schedules or recent game dates that one team would have a significant rest advantage over the other leading into this game.\n\nThis analysis is based on the bye week schedules and recent game dates provided by credible sources[3][4].', '[\"https:\\/\\/www.foxsports.com\\/articles\\/nfl\\/titans-vs-jaguars-2024-prediction-odds-picks-dec-8\",\"https:\\/\\/www.foxsports.com\\/stories\\/nfl\\/nfl-bye-weeks\",\"https:\\/\\/www.nbcsportsphiladelphia.com\\/nfl\\/nfl-bye-weeks-breakdown-2024\\/616252\\/\",\"https:\\/\\/www.foxsports.com\\/nfl\\/week-14-jacksonville-jaguars-vs-tennessee-titans-dec-08-2024-game-boxscore-10455\",\"https:\\/\\/www.bleachernat