(1786, 'Investigate any external factors such as travel schedules, rest days, or back-to-back games affecting either team.', 'External Factors Analysis Agent', 'Low', '2024-12-08 19:27:18', 47, 1, 'To analyze the external factors affecting the NBA game between the Memphis Grizzlies and the Boston Celtics on Saturday, December 7th, here are some factual points gathered from credible sources:\n\n## Travel Schedules and Rest Days\n- The Memphis Grizzlies played the Celtics on December 7th, which was part of their road trip. Before this game, the Grizzlies had a game against the Sacramento Kings on December 5th, giving them a couple of days of rest and travel time[2][3].\n- After the game against the Celtics, the Grizzlies were scheduled to play the Washington Wizards on December 8th, indicating a back-to-back game scenario for the Grizzlies[2][3].\n\n## Recent Games and Performance\n- The Boston Celtics, prior to the game on December 7th, did not have any back-to-back games immediately preceding this match. However, their next game is scheduled for December 12th against the Detroit Pistons, providing them with a few days of rest after the Grizzlies game[1].\n\n## Game Outcomes\n- The Grizzlies won the game against the Celtics with a score of 127-121, despite the back-to-back game scenario they were facing with the upcoming game against the Wizards[1][4].\n\nIn summary:\n- The Memphis Grizzlies had a couple of days of rest before the December 7th game against the Celtics but were facing a back-to-back game scenario with the Wizards on December 8th.\n- The Boston Celtics had a few days of rest before their next game after the match against the Grizzlies.\n\nThese factors indicate that while the Grizzlies had some rest before the game, they were still in a challenging back-to-back game situation, whereas the Celtics had more rest time both before and after the game.', '[\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=rJ5As1SMCUw\",\"https:\\/\\/www.cbssports.com\\/nba\\/teams\\/M