(1787, 'Review expert analysis and statistical models that predict game outcomes based on factual data models.', 'Statistical Analysis Agent', 'Medium', '2024-12-08 19:27:18', 47, 1, 'To provide a factual and evidence-based analysis of the NBA game between the Memphis Grizzlies and the Boston Celtics on December 7, 2024, here are the key points from credible sources:\n\n## Game Outcome\n- The Memphis Grizzlies won the game against the Boston Celtics with a final score of 127-121[2][5].\n\n## Performance Statistics\n- Ja Morant of the Grizzlies scored 32 points, had 9 assists, and 9 rebounds.\n- Jaren Jackson Jr. of the Grizzlies added 27 points and 9 rebounds.\n- Jrue Holiday of the Celtics scored 23 points, while Jaylen Brown and Payton Pritchard each scored 22 points[2][5].\n\n## Team Performance\n- The Grizzlies shot 50.0% from the field (47-94) and 45.5% from the 3-point line (15-33).\n- The Celtics shot 40.0% from the field (42-105) and 30.0% from the 3-point line (18-60)[2].\n\n## Historical Context\n- This win marked the Grizzlies\' first victory in TD Garden since November 27, 2013, and snapped their 10-game losing streak in Boston[2][5].\n\n## Predictive Models Before the Game\n- Prior to the game, predictive models suggested the Celtics were more likely to win. For example, Dimers\' advanced NBA model predicted a 72% chance of the Celtics winning, with a predicted final score of 122-115 in favor of the Celtics[4].\n\nThis summary is based on verifiable data and official reports from the game, avoiding any speculative predictions.', '[\"https:\\/\\/www.cmegroup.com\\/education\\/courses\\/introduction-to-futures\\/understanding-the-role-of-speculators.html\",\"https:\\/\\/www.cbssports.com\\/nba\\/gametracker\\/recap\\/NBA_20241207_MEM@BOS\\/\",\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=50QHBFUgcE0\",\"https:\\/\\/www.dimers.com\\/news\\/memphis-grizzlies-vs-boston-celtics-prediction-nba-ac-december-7-2024\",\"https:\\/\\/www.espn.com\\/nba\\/recap\\/_\\/gameI