(1813, 'Investigate any significant recent changes in team rosters or management that could influence game performance.', 'Team Dynamics Analysis Agent', 'Medium', '2024-12-08 19:39:14', 40, 1, 'To assess the potential impact of recent roster changes on the game performance of the Chicago Bears and the San Francisco 49ers for their matchup on Sunday, December 8th, here are some significant recent changes in their rosters:\n\n### San Francisco 49ers\n\n- **December 4, 2024**: The 49ers elevated RB Patrick Taylor from the practice squad to the active roster and placed DT Kevin Givens on injured reserve. They also signed RB Ke\'Shawn Vaughn to the practice squad[1].\n- **December 3, 2024**: The 49ers claimed RB Israel Abanikanda off waivers from the New York Jets and signed WR Ronnie Bell to the practice squad[1].\n- **December 2, 2024**: The team placed RBs Christian McCaffrey and Jordan Mason on injured reserve, which could significantly impact their running game[1].\n- **November 23, 2024**: The 49ers elevated LB Jalen Graham and CB Nick McCloud from the practice squad to the active roster and signed S Tashaun Gipson Sr. to the active roster. They also placed LB Tatum Bethune on injured reserve[1].\n- **November 25, 2024**: The 49ers declined to activate C Jon Feliciano from injured reserve, ending his season[1].\n\n### Chicago Bears\n\n- **October 26, 2024**: The Bears cut FB Khari Blasingame, WR Velus Jones Jr., and DB Tarvarius Moore was moved to the active/practice squad[2].\n- **October 24, 2024**: The Bears added TE Joel Wilson to the practice squad and deleted TE Tommy Sweeney from the practice squad[2].\n- **October 15, 2024**: The Bears added LS Jake McQuaide and DE Jamree Kromah to the practice squad, while deleting DT Travis Bell from the practice squad[2].\n- **September 21, 2024**: The Bears moved WR Collin Johnson between the active and practice squads, and RB Travis Homer was placed on IR with a finger injury[2].\n- There have been no recent significa