(1816, 'Analyze the offensive and defensive line matchups for both teams to identify potential advantages.', 'Matchup Analysis Agent', 'Medium', '2024-12-08 19:39:14', 40, 1, 'To analyze the offensive and defensive line matchups for the NFL game between the Chicago Bears and the San Francisco 49ers on December 8, 2024, here are some key factual points from credible sources:\n\n## Offense - San Francisco 49ers\n\n- **Quarterback:** Brock Purdy has thrown for 2,707 yards, 13 touchdowns, and eight interceptions, averaging 246.1 yards per game and 8.4 yards per attempt. He also has 271 rushing yards and four rushing touchdowns[1][2].\n- **Receiving:** George Kittle leads with 649 receiving yards and eight touchdowns, while Jauan Jennings has 684 yards and four touchdowns. Deebo Samuel has 531 receiving yards and one touchdown[1][2].\n- **Rushing:** The 49ers\' primary rusher is Jordan Mason, who has 789 yards and three touchdowns on 153 carries[2].\n\n## Offense - Chicago Bears\n\n- **Quarterback:** Caleb Williams has passed for 2,612 yards, 14 touchdowns, and five interceptions, averaging 217.7 yards per game and 6.4 yards per attempt. He also has 372 rushing yards[1][2].\n- **Rushing:** D\'Andre Swift is the leading rusher with 704 yards and five touchdowns on 179 carries. Swift also has 313 receiving yards on 33 catches[1][2].\n- **Receiving:** D.J. Moore has 663 receiving yards and five touchdowns on 62 catches, while Keenan Allen has 441 yards and five touchdowns on 44 catches[1][2].\n\n## Defense - San Francisco 49ers\n\n- **Linebackers:** Fred Warner has 88 tackles, 3.0 tackles for loss (TFL), one sack, and two interceptions. Nick Bosa has 36 tackles, 10.0 TFL, seven sacks, and one interception. Leonard Floyd contributes with 34 tackles, 6.0 TFL, and 6.5 sacks[1].\n- **Secondary:** Deommodore Lenoir has 67 tackles, 2.0 TFL, and two interceptions[1].\n\n## Defense - Chicago Bears\n\n- **Pass Defense:** The Bears allow 209.4 passing yards per game, ranking 11th in 