ile the 49ers have one of the worst red zone defenses, allowing 70.7% of red zone possessions to result in touchdowns[1].\n- The Bears have had success in converting third downs, with 22 conversions in their last three games, which is tied for the most in the league over that period[1].\n\nWhile these points do not provide a detailed quarter-by-quarter breakdown, they highlight some key trends:\n- The Bears tend to keep games close but struggle to win, suggesting they may have strong quarters but falter in others.\n- The 49ers have had significant defensive issues, particularly in the red zone, and their recent losses indicate potential lapses in performance throughout games.\n\nFor a more precise analysis of scoring patterns by quarter, detailed game-by-game statistics would be necessary, which are not provided in the available sources.', '[\"https:\\/\\/www.si.com\\/nfl\\/bears\\/chicago-bears-and-san-francisco-49ers-game-day-preview\",\"https:\\/\\/www.49erswebzone.com\\/alltimescores\\/opponent\\/chicago+bears\\/\",\"https:\\/\\/www.si.com\\/nfl\\/49ers\\/news\\/49ers-bears-game-preview-time-for-a-pride-check-01jeknmr0swm\",\"https:\\/\\/www.cbssports.com\\/nfl\\/gametracker\\/live\\/NFL_20241208_CHI@SF\\/\",\"https:\\/\\/www.49erswebzone.com\\/articles\\/186894-transcripts-shanahan-updates-49ers-bears-matchup\\/\"]'),
