(1862, 'Examine game-winning drives completed by the Falcons and Vikings in the fourth quarter across the last three years.', 'Historical Analysis Agent', 'Medium', '2024-12-08 20:22:17', 54, 1, 'To examine the game-winning drives completed by the Atlanta Falcons and the Minnesota Vikings in the fourth quarter over the last three years, we need to look at historical data on game-winning drives.\n\n## Game-Winning Drives Data\n\nThe data on game-winning drives is available from Pro-Football-Reference.com, which provides a comprehensive list of game-winning drives by quarterbacks since 1950.\n\n### Atlanta Falcons\n- For the 2022 season, the Falcons\' primary quarterback was Marcus Mariota and later Desmond Ridder. According to the data, in 2022, Mariota had 1 game-winning drive, and Ridder did not have any[5].\n- In the 2021 season, Matt Ryan was the primary quarterback for the Falcons. He had 2 game-winning drives that year[5].\n- For the 2020 season, Matt Ryan also had 2 game-winning drives[5].\n\n### Minnesota Vikings\n- For the 2022 season, the Vikings\' primary quarterback was Kirk Cousins, who had 8 game-winning drives, one of the highest in the league that year[5].\n- In the 2021 season, Kirk Cousins had 2 game-winning drives[5].\n- For the 2020 season, Kirk Cousins had 2 game-winning drives as well[5].\n\n## Summary of Fourth Quarter Performance\n- **Kirk Cousins (Vikings):**\n  - 2022: 8 game-winning drives\n  - 2021: 2 game-winning drives\n  - 2020: 2 game-winning drives\n- **Atlanta Falcons Quarterbacks:**\n  - 2022: 1 game-winning drive (Mariota)\n  - 2021: 2 game-winning drives (Matt Ryan)\n  - 2020: 2 game-winning drives (Matt Ryan)\n\nBased on the data, Kirk Cousins of the Minnesota Vikings has significantly more game-winning drives in the fourth quarter over the last three years compared to the quarterbacks of the Atlanta Falcons.\n\n## Conclusion\nThe Minnesota Vikings, led by Kirk Cousins, have demonstrated a stronger performance in terms of game-wi