(1893, 'Analyze the historical head-to-head performance between the Seahawks and the Cardinals.', 'Historical Analysis Agent', 'High', '2024-12-08 21:06:32', 56, 1, 'To analyze the historical head-to-head performance between the Seattle Seahawks and the Arizona Cardinals, here are the key factual points gathered from credible sources:\n\n## Overall Head-to-Head Record\n- The Seattle Seahawks lead the overall series with a record of 28-22-1 against the Arizona Cardinals[1][3][5].\n\n## Recent Performance\n- In the last 10 games, the Seahawks have a record of 7-3 against the Cardinals[1][3].\n- The Seahawks are currently on a 6-game winning streak against the Cardinals, which started on January 9, 2022, with a 38-30 win[1][3][5].\n\n## Recent Games\n- The most recent game between the two teams was on November 24, 2024, where the Seahawks won 16-6 at home against the Cardinals[1][3][5].\n- In the 2023 season, the Seahawks swept both games against the Cardinals, winning 20-10 at home in Week 7 and 21-20 on the road in Week 18[1][3].\n\n## Historical Streaks\n- The longest all-time winning streak for the Seahawks against the Cardinals is the current 6-game streak. For the Cardinals, their longest winning streak was 5 games, which occurred from 1976 to 1995[1][3][5].\n\n## Playoff Meetings\n- The Seahawks and Cardinals have never met in the NFL playoffs[1][3][5].\n\n## Largest Victories\n- The Seahawks\' largest victory was 58-0 in 2012, while the Cardinals\' largest victory was 27-3 in 2009[5].\n\nThis summary provides a factual basis for understanding the historical performance between the Seahawks and the Cardinals, without speculating on the outcome of future games.', '[\"https:\\/\\/champsorchumps.us\\/team\\/nfl\\/seattle-seahawks\\/head-to-head\\/arizona-cardinals\",\"https:\\/\\/www.cmegroup.com\\/education\\/courses\\/introduction-to-futures\\/understanding-the-role-of-speculators.html\",\"https:\\/\\/champsorchumps.us\\/team\\/nfl\\/arizona-cardinals\\/head-to-h