ptured on social media mirrored electoral outcomes, indicating reliable reflections of public preferences.\"\n            },\n            \"Campaign Strategies\": {\n                \"Key Findings\": \"Dissanayake capitalized on anti-corruption rhetoric. Wickremesinghe emphasized stability, Premadasa focused on economic relief.\",\n                \"Probability Score\": 70,\n                \"Rationale\": \"Campaign messages aligned well with voter expectations but the anti-establishment narrative had a larger pull.\"\n            },\n            \"Key Issues\": {\n                \"Key Findings\": \"Economic crisis heavily influenced voter preferences. Candidates leveraged economic hardship narratives to sway voters.\",\n                \"Probability Score\": 85,\n                \"Rationale\": \"Economic adversity was a prevalent theme affecting voter preferences directly.\"\n            },\n            \"Opinion Polls\": {\n                \"Key Findings\": \"Polls indicated a consistent lead for Dissanayake, reflecting strong public sentiment toward his leadership.\",\n                \"Probability Score\": 90,\n                \"Rationale\": \"Polling data accurately predicted electoral outcome demonstrating effectiveness and reliability.\"\n            },\n            \"International Relations\": {\n                \"Key Findings\": \"Candidate strategy incorporated IMF pressures and regional dynamics. India played a notable indirect role.\",\n                \"Probability Score\": 60,\n                \"Rationale\": \"While important, international relations had less direct influence than economic policies.\"\n            },\n            \"Incumbent Performance\": {\n                \"Key Findings\": \"Critiques centered on economic crisis handling. Dissanayake offered contrasting governance reform promises.\",\n                \"Probability Score\": 75,\n                \"Rationale\": \"Past performance greatly impacted voter perception but was overshadowed 