(12, 'Why are proxy networks fundementally valuable if they are built onchain? Consider the stablecoin narrative vs money in a bank. In one, it\'s permissionless, in the other, it\'s permissioned. One has yeild built in and people can transact on then, the other doesn\'t etc. so the blockchian has native advatages. What does a Proxy network have like that beyond just simply prvenance, reputation, identity and things. Like what are the real advantages of building a proxy network onchain?', '{\n    \"Summary\": {\n        \"Overview\": \"On-chain proxy networks offer significant advantages over traditional systems due to their decentralized, permissionless nature. These advantages include enhanced security, transparency, scalability, and efficiency in cross-border payments. However, they face challenges related to regulation, environmental impact, and complexity.\",\n        \"Overall Probability Score\": 85\n    },\n    \"Key Insights and Implications\": \"On-chain proxy networks capitalize on blockchain\'s inherent transparency, security, and decentralized advantages, making them fundamentally valuable for applications like cross-border payments, privacy enhancement, and user engagement through token-based incentives. They face challenges in terms of legal compliance, environmental impacts, and complexity, which need to be carefully managed. These networks are poised to change financial inclusivity by integrating into the global financial system, but require clear regulatory frameworks to maximize their potential.\",\n    \"Thematic Breakdown\": {\n        \"Primary Advantages of On-Chain Architecture\": {\n            \"Key Findings\": \"Advantages like transparency, decentralization, and security make on-chain proxy networks vital for secure and fair data transmission.\",\n            \"Probability Score\": 90,\n            \"Rationale\": \"These elements are directly enabled by blockchain technology, crucial for the decentralized identity and security required in